# Git & Version Control

## Semantic Commits
- Use semantic commit messages: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`, `style:`, `test:`, `chore:`
- Follow the pattern: `type(scope): description`
- Examples: `feat(contact): add form validation`, `fix(api): resolve curl error`
